{"EXTEMPORAL":[{"def":"Extemporaneous; unpremeditated.","pos":""}],"EXTEMPORANEAN":[{"def":"Ex*tem`po*ra\"ne*an, a.","pos":""}],"EXTEMPORANEOUS":[{"def":"Composed, performed, or uttered on the spur of the moment, or without previous study; unpremeditated; off-hand; extempore; extemporary; as, an extemporaneous address or production.","pos":""}],"EXTEMPORARILY":[{"def":"Extemporaneously.","pos":""}],"EXTEMPORARY":[{"def":"Made for the occasion; for the time being.","pos":""}],"EXTEMPORE":[{"def":"Without previous study or meditation; without preparation; on the spur of the moment; suddenly; extemporaneously; as, to write or speak extempore.","pos":""},{"def":"Done or performed extempore.","pos":""}],"EXTEMPORINESS":[{"def":"The quality of being done or devised extempore [Obs.","pos":""}],"EXTEMPORIZATION":[{"def":"The act of extemporizing; the act of doing anything extempore.","pos":""}],"EXTEMPORIZE":[{"def":"To speak extempore; especially, to discourse without special preparation; to make an offhand address.","pos":""}],"EXTEMPORIZER":[{"def":"One who extemporizes.","pos":""}],"EXTEND":[{"def":"To value, as lands taken by a writ of extent in satisfaction of a debt; to assign by writ of extent.","pos":""}],"EXTENDEDLY":[{"def":"In an extended manner.","pos":""}],"EXTENDER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, extends or stretches anything.","pos":""}],"EXTENDIBLE":[{"def":"Liable to be taken by a writ of extent.","pos":""}],"EXTENDLESSNESS":[{"def":"Unlimited extension.","pos":""}],"EXTENSE":[{"def":"Outreaching; expansive; extended, superficially or otherwise.","pos":""}],"EXTENSIBILITY":[{"def":"The quality of being extensible; the capacity of being extended; as, the extensibility of a fiber, or of a plate of metal.","pos":""}],"EXTENSIBLE":[{"def":"Capable of being extended, whether in length or breadth; susceptible of enlargement; extensible; extendible; -- the opposite of contractible or compressible.","pos":""}],"EXTENSIBLENESS":[{"def":"Ex*ten\"si*ble*ness, n.","pos":""}],"EXTENSILE":[{"def":"Suited for, or capable of, extension; extensible.","pos":""}],"EXTENSION":[{"def":"That property of a body by which it occupies a portion of space.","pos":""},{"def":"Capacity of a concept or general term to include a greater or smaller number of objects; -- correlative of intension.","pos":""}],"EXTENSIONAL":[{"def":"Having great extent.","pos":""}],"EXTENSIONIST":[{"def":"One who favors or advocates extension.","pos":""}],"EXTENSIVE":[{"def":"Having wide extent; of much superficial extent; expanded; large; broad; wide; comprehensive; as, an extensive farm; an extensive lake; an extensive sphere of operations; extensive benevolence; extensive greatness.","pos":""},{"def":"Capable of being extended.","pos":""}],"EXTENSIVELY":[{"def":"To a great extent; widely; largely; as, a story is extensively circulated.","pos":""}],"EXTENSIVENESS":[{"def":"The state of being extensive; wideness; largeness; extent; diffusiveness.","pos":""}],"EXTENSOMETER":[{"def":"An instrument for measuring the extension of a body, especially for measuring the elongation of bars of iron, steel, or other material, when subjected to a tensile force.","pos":""}],"EXTENSOR":[{"def":"A muscle which serves to extend or straighten any part of the body, as an arm or a finger; -- opposed to flexor.","pos":""}],"EXTENT":[{"def":"Space or degree to which a thing is extended; hence, superficies; compass; bulk; size; length; as, an extent of country or of line; extent of information or of charity.","pos":""},{"def":"Degree; measure; proportion.","pos":""}],"EXTENUATE":[{"def":"To make thin or slender; to draw out so as to lessen the thickness.","pos":""},{"def":"To lessen; to palliate; to lessen or weaken the force of; to diminish the conception of, as crime, guilt, faults, ills, accusations, etc.","pos":""}],"EXTENUATION":[{"def":"The act of axtenuating or the state of being extenuated; the act of making thin, slender, or lean, or of palliating; diminishing, or lessening; palliation, as of a crime; mitigation, as of punishment.","pos":""}],"EXTENUATOR":[{"def":"One who extenuates.","pos":""}],"EXTENUATORY":[{"def":"Tending to extenuate or palliate.","pos":""}],"EXTERIOR":[{"def":"External; outward; pertaining to that which is external; -- opposed to interior; as, the exterior part of a sphere.","pos":""},{"def":"External; on the outside; without the limits of; extrinsic; as, an object exterior to a man, opposed to what is within, or in his mind.","pos":""}],"EXTERIORITY":[{"def":"Surface; superficies; externality.","pos":""}],"EXTERIORLY":[{"def":"Outwardly; externally; on the exterior.","pos":""}],"EXTERMINATE":[{"def":"To eliminate, as unknown quantities.","pos":""}],"EXTERMINATION":[{"def":"The act of exterminating; total destruction; eradication; excision; as, the extermination of inhabitants or tribes, of error or vice, or of weeds from a field.","pos":""}],"EXTERMINATOR":[{"def":"One who, or that which, exterminates.","pos":""}],"EXTERMINATORY":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to extermination; tending to exterminate.","pos":""}],"EXTERMINE":[{"def":"To exterminate; to destroy.","pos":""}],"EXTERN":[{"def":"External; outward; not inherent.","pos":""}],"EXTERNAL":[{"def":"Away from the mesial plane of the body; lateral.","pos":""}],"EXTERNALISM":[{"def":"That philosophy or doctrine which recognizes or deals only with externals, or objects of sense perception; positivism; phenomenalism.","pos":""}],"EXTERNALISTIC":[{"def":"Pertaining to externalism North Am.","pos":""}],"EXTERNALITY":[{"def":"State of being external; exteriority; (Metaph.","pos":""},{"def":"separation from the perceiving mind.","pos":""}],"EXTERNALIZE":[{"def":"To make external; to manifest by outward form.","pos":""}],"EXTERNALLY":[{"def":"In an external manner; outwardly; on the outside; in appearance; visibly.","pos":""}],"EXTERNE":[{"def":"An officer in attendance upon a hospital, but not residing in it; esp.","pos":""}],"EXTERRANEOUS":[{"def":"Foreign; belonging to, or coming from, abroad.","pos":""}],"EXTERRITORIAL":[{"def":"Beyond the territorial limits; foreign to, or exempt from, the territorial jurisdiction.","pos":""}],"EXTERRITORIALITY":[{"def":"The state of being beyond the limits of a country.","pos":""},{"def":"The state of being free from the jurisdiction of a country when within its territorial limits.","pos":""}],"EXTERSION":[{"def":"The act of wiping or rubbing out.","pos":""}]}